Handson3 - Angular Directives and Pipes
Task 1: Structural Directives

Goal: Control DOM using *ngIf, *ngFor and *ngSwitch.

1. HomeComponent/CourseListComponent
isLoading = true;

ngOnInit(){
  setTimeout(()=>{ this.isLoading=false; },1500);
}

Template:
<p *ngIf="isLoading">Loading courses...</p>

<ng-template #noCourses>
  <p>No courses available.</p>
</ng-template>

<div *ngIf="courses.length; else noCourses">
  <app-course-card
      *ngFor="let course of courses; let i=index; trackBy: trackByCourseId">
  </app-course-card>
</div>

trackByCourseId(index:number,course:any){
  return course.id;
}

Status:
<div [ngSwitch]="course.gradeStatus">
 <span *ngSwitchCase="'passed'">Passed</span>
 <span *ngSwitchCase="'failed'">Failed</span>
 <span *ngSwitchDefault>Pending</span>
</div>

Expected:
• Loading message for 1.5 sec
• Courses displayed using *ngFor
• ngSwitch shows Passed/Failed/Pending
• Empty list shows 'No courses available.'

